        | or 50 Million tokens total. 
      p In	future	ICOs,	the	price	per	token	will	be	determined	through	a	bidding	process	of	interested	buyers.	We’ll	sell	tokens	in	a	similar	way	that	Google	sells	ads	-- using	a	
        a(href="#") Vickrey	auction.
      p The price per token is $0.005. 
      p The First Token Sale cap is $250,000. 
      hr
      .button-group
        button.button-back.button-primary(data-step='step-4')
          i.ion-chevron-left
          | Back
        button.button-next.button-primary(data-step='step-6')
          | Next
          i.ion-chevron-right
            
    .email-steps.step-6
      p As	of	July	2017,	the	lower	bound	transaction	cost	on	Ethereum	is	$0.14.	It’s	$2.46	for	Bitcoin.
      p We’re	designing	the	Storecoin	protocol	for	transactions	to	be	free	while	the	network	remains	secure.
      p To keep transaction costs on Storecoin free, the storecoin token supply will increase
        | by a maximum of 5% per year. This 5% will pay for the operation costs and the
        | transaction costs of the blockchain protocol.	
      p If	the	5%	token	supply	maximum	is	reached,	then	transaction	costs	will	be	passed	on	to	senders	through	a	mechanism	similar	to	gas	on	Ethereum.	
      p We’ll share these economics, our consensus protocol, and how we secure our
        | consensus in the upcoming Storecoin Whitepaper. We’re in deep R&D now.
      hr
      .button-group
        button.button-back.button-primary(data-step='step-5')
          i.ion-chevron-left
          | Back
        button.button-next.button-primary(data-step='step-7')
          | Next
          i.ion-chevron-right
            
    .email-steps.step-7
